Look your last on your dearest ones,<br>
Brothers and husbands, fathers and sons:<br>
Swift they go to the ravenous stuns,<br>
The gluttonous stuns of war.<br>
<br>
Everywhere thrill the air<br>
The maniac bells of war.<br>
There will be little of sleeping tonight;<br>
Death's red sickle is reaping to-night:<br>
War! War! War!<br>
